org.spongepowered.api.entity.living.player

Interface User

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ArmorEquipable, Carrier, CompositeValueStore<DataHolder,DataManipulator<?,?>>, Contextual, DataHolder, DataSerializable, Equipable, Identifiable, PropertyHolder, Subject, Tamer, ValueContainer<DataHolder>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Player

    public interface User
extends DataHolder, ArmorEquipable, Tamer, Subject
    A User is the data usually associated with a Player that is persisted across server restarts. This is in contrast to Player which represents the in-game entity associated with an online User.

      • setLocation

        boolean setLocation(com.flowpowered.math.vector.Vector3d position,
                    UUID world)
        Sets the position and world of this User.

        The UUID must belong to an existing world.

        When the User isOnline() this redirects to Entity.setLocation(Location)

        Parameters:
        position - The position to set
        world - The world UUID to set
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - When the UUID does not belong to an existing world.
